> Letting out a hiss, DINOBOT also put it out along the communicator, "The
> volcano is ejecting, all PREDACONS retreat to base at best possible speed to
> regroup."  THey would come in search of HYDRAS and CRYOTEK later, but for
> now extricating themselvse and self preservation was the highest priority!
>
> VICE GRIP sending out a communication <Recover the injured and carry them as
> best able.  Disengage and do not fire upon the Maximals or any others.  USe
> the smoke as cover."  Of course, everyone was going nearly blind on
> electronics..  "Spread out the orders along genral frequencies to spread out
> our communication range, act as individualized relays."

<NEW>

SKYSHADOW who was already putting out similar orders was taking his
men out of the area, fording their way through the darkening skies.
There was no way to stop the volcano, not that the PREDACONS cared one
way oir another. Their only choice was to flee, and flee they did.

Even BLACKARACHNIA, if she chose, would be in range for such a call as
the rest of the troop moved out.

It took them some time to retrace their steps and find their way back
through the jungle paths and out.

The trip back was relatively uneventful. The Volcano behind them was
quickly becoming a distant memory as they set their optics on getting
home, recharging, performing repairs on themselves and fowarding
varies nefarious schemes.

Just as they were topping the last rise that would bring HYDRAS' base
into view there was a crackle along the PREDACON encrypted channels.
"Welcom back." It was TARANTULUS' voice. "I am not detecting Hydras
among you." There was a certain eagerness in his voice. "Or Cryotek
for that matter."

There was a wicked chuckle, "Have you done away with the trouble makers?"

(TAG)

- Preston
